info.description:
Need FaviconizeTab extension.

Normal: Only selected tab with title, other faviconized.

Hover other tab: Show text.

Configuration FaviconizeTab:
<-----------------
tab[faviconized="true"] {
   min-width: 36px;
   max-width: 36px;
}

tab[faviconized="true"] .tab-text,
tab[faviconized="true"] .tab-close-button {
   display: none;
}
------------->

Paste this in extensions/faviconizetab@espion.just-size.jp/content/faviconizetab.css

In FaviconizeTab's preferences:
-in auto faviconize tab sections: write '*'

style.css:
@namespace url(http://www.mozilla.org/keymaster/gatekeeper/there.is.only.xul);

/*Jakub Tymejczyk*/

tab[faviconized="true"] {
   min-width: 28px !important;
   max-width: 28px !important;
}

tab[selected="true"] {
   min-width: 250px !important;
   max-width: 250px !important;
}

tab[selected="false"]:hover {
   min-width: 200px !important;
   max-width: 200px !important;
}

tab[faviconized="true"] .tab-text,
tab[faviconized="true"] .tab-close-button {
   display: none !important;
}

.tabbrowser-tab[selected="false"]:hover .tab-close-button{
display: inline !important;
}

tab[selected="true"] .tab-text,
tab[selected="true"] .tab-close-button,
.tabbrowser-tab[selected="false"] .tab-text,
.tabbrowser-tab[selected="false"]:hover .tab-text,
.tabbrowser-tab[selected="false"]:hover .tab-text {
display: block !important;
}
